-- Canada Dollar Falls for Fourth Day in Longest Losing Streak Since January
-- James Holloway
-- 2010-06-24T17:59:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/loonie-appreciates-versus-greenback-on-bets-recent-weakness-overdone.html

          
          
             The Canadian dollar erased its
decline versus its U.S. counterpart as stocks pared losses. The
currency, known as the loonie, traded at $1.0381 in Toronto,
from C$1.0397 yesterday. It earlier fell as much as much as 0.7
percent.  
          
          


  


        